# Session, git, and documentation

## Session closeout (`/sluta`, `/final-sweep`, `/finals-weep`)

Closes **this session‚Äôs** work. Order: (1) `git status` + `git diff` [+ `--staged`], fix only this scope (2) lint / `npx tsc --noEmit` if many files (3) `docs/` only if behavior or public surface changed ‚Äî see **Docs & plans** below (4) save (5) stage **only your session‚Äôs files** (6) commit ‚Äî PowerShell git: **`platform-quirks.mdc`** (7) `git push`. If `.cursor/agent-intents/BOARD.md` exists, check overlapping `active` before commit. Explicit permission to commit/push **this scope**; do not commit others‚Äô in-progress work.

## Agent intent and parallel work

**Board:** `.cursor/agent-intents/BOARD.md` ‚Äî read before editing shared areas; add/update your entry (`active` ‚Üí `done`), unique **Agent** handle (not raw model name), narrow **Touching**, heartbeat on same local date = fresh; never remove another agent‚Äôs `active` row; stale ‚Üí `stale-suspect` or remove.

**Overlap:** Unexpected diffs or active board rows ‚Üí assume parallel work; narrow scope, re-read files, **stage only your files**, ask before ambiguous edits. Never overwrite/commit others‚Äô work without confirmation.

**Push (`origin/master`):** Before `git push`: `git fetch origin` and `git pull` (or `git pull --rebase origin master`). Principles: [`docs/plans/active/PROJECT-STATE-AND-DIRECTION.md`](../../docs/plans/active/PROJECT-STATE-AND-DIRECTION.md) ¬ß6.

